lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The most hated mage to the ben order</span><hr size=1> Hmm.  I suppose you haven't forgotten my rash posts from September.  I am leaving this post as a public apology for what I had done some time back.  I ended up giving my account to my younger brother while I went to a job out west as an apprenticeship.  I have returned to school now and I am back playing with a new guild. (he didn't like EQ.  He is more of a Quake fan)<br>
<br>
Now to tell you why I was such a prick.  <br>
<br>
Recently (september) my grandfather passed away.  We were very close and I had just settled into my new appartment living on my own away from family and friends.  It was hard to get back on my feet emotionally and I engrossed myself in study and in EQ unfortunately.  I had just gotten off my previous work term and was excited to get back to school with some buddies and get back in this guild.  Only now I can come to type up this message without nearly crying or wanting to destroy something.  At first I didn't want to get back in the guild cause I was not myself.  Then suddenly I decided that since all of my buddies from school failed first year and did not return I would come back to a guild that seemed the best thing for me at the time so that I could keep my mind off of my problems and keep in the &quot;game&quot; (more or less sanity).  When I finally asked a member to try to find me an officer so I could officially get back in they kinda told me where to go...  I know that it sounded like I was barking orders and I deserved the response I got and I realize that now my head is less garbled.  So (being a guy who never gives up to any emotion but rage) I acted on it and became a total idiot and tried to seek some sort of revenge.  It is always easy to hate, even over the littlest things.  So I now completely apologize to that person (most of us know who I mean) and to the guild for using the guild board as my way of venting my emotions out.  I do not seek redemption or membership or anything but in RL I am a modest man and I hate to have any enemies because I don't have any enemies in my life. (not that I know of or created).  So now since I remembered how I acted I am here to say sorry and you can be the judge.  There is no excuse for my actions because it is not like I just said it.  I actually typed it.  Believe me or not it really doesn't matter I suppose.  After all we are just a bunch of people who want a brief escape from real life worries and have a little fun.  So now if you see me in game it is the original Faadno. (the jerk to some I suppose)  I hope you didn't see the name Faadno around and thought that it was me pretending not to know who you are because my bro really doesn't know who any of you are.<br>
<br>
Once again sorry.<br>
I hope this message doesn't make you hate me even more but it is the only way I can get in contact with you all and set things straight.  I also realize that maybe it doesn't matter if I say sorry to a bunch of fictional characters but then I come to realize that the people behind the character are real.<br>
<br>
Good adventuring to you all.<br>
<br>
Faadno Elementus<br>
31st level mage<br>
